inn1.comm: wide of the crease, angling outside off, on a length, defended to cover
dug in short, gets it to rise chest high, left alone outside off
short of a length, pitches on off, angling away, left alone
short of a length, pitches on off, angles away, defended towards mid-off
this one is pitched outside leg, and Farhat clips it away past midwicket for two

Bravo the captain. Dives in front of first slip to send Farhat back. Nothing shot really. Pushes at a length ball, away from the body. It angles away, takes a healthy edge, and is headed for a comfortable take for Gayle at first slip when Bravo dives to his right and takes it one-handed
straightens up outside off, but not close enough to the stumps to make him play
short, angling away, left alone, called a wide
left alone outside off. Again it shapes back in, but is not close enough
short of a length, outside off, punched to point
fuller, outside off, left alone through to the keeper
another leave outsaide off. Jamshed watchful here
short of a length, too wide, called again
another wide delivery, but not wide enough to be called
short, wide, cut away hard, on the half-volley to Pollard at point. Was that a drop? Not sure if it carried. I can tell you it was very low, but might just have reached him on the yorker length
defended off the back foot as Roach bangs this one in
fuller, angling in, 140ks, defended back to him
short of a length, angling in from wide of the crease. Defended back to him
this one seams back in from well outside off, hits him high on the pad after beating the inside edge
short of a length, outside off, the defensive shot finishes the maiden
short, wide, would have been called wide had Jamshed not stretched out to cut this to the left of point
this is closer to the stumps, and Jamshed stays back to defend
short of a length, outside off, defended with an open face
on a length, outside off, left alone
short of a length, tucked away off the hip
beauty. The first time Rampaul has bowled to a right-hand batsman, and he has bowled a gem. Angling in towards off, but seaming away from just short of a length. Beats the edge
full, on the pads, pushed past midwicket for one

beautiful shot. Square-drive on the up. Pure. Short of a length, outside off, he presses forward, is nowhere near the pitch of the ball, but his hands do the job for him, keeping it down and placing it to the right of point

Roach strikes back. Timber. Goes wide of the crease, fires in a quick full delivery. There is no swing or seam on this, but Hafeez has completely missed the line. Hit plumb on the back foot before the ball ricochets onto the stumps
oh hello. Dug in short, Shafiq is not equal to it. Hit on the glove
fuller, outside off, defended to cover
short again, and he has hit the shoulder of Shafiq's bat as he defends
short of a length, on off, defended off the back foot
wide length ball, Jamshed goes after it, and is beaten
short of a length, outside off, left alone
on a length, defended off the back foot, just outside off
short, wide, extra bounce beats him on the cut. Called wide, though
length ball outside off, holds its line, left alone again
short of a length, pitches outside off, angles away. Left alone

the short ball has got Shafiq. Hit on the glove once, hit on the shoulder of the bat once, and now he has cut this straight to third man. Roach bounces him again, it is about shoulder high, with a short leg in place. Shafiq hasn't been leaving them alone, and the fend with a short leg in place can be dangerous. So he cuts, and cuts in the air, straight down third man's throat. Superb move to bring the short leg in
another bouncer. It's accurate, and not too high. It's seaming back in too. Misbah does well to drop his wrists
short of a length, outside off, left alone
short of a length, left alone even though it is angling back in. Misses the stumps comfortably
end of a wicket-maiden. Short of a length, rising towards the chest. Misbah fends with soft hands
short of a length, angling in, hits him high on the pad. Another wicket-maiden
short of a length, outside off, left alone
short of a length, outside off, pushed to cover-point
punched off the back foot, past cover-point for first runs off the bat in 19 balls
length ball outside off, defended off the back foot
this one swings back in a touch, and Nasir defends off the back foot
short of a length, outside off, defended off the back foot
short of a length, angling in, defended in front of off
bouncer. Outside off, Misbah ducks under it
short of a length, outside off, defended to cover
angling in from wide of the crease, defended with soft hands again

huge appeal for lbw. And Bravo is reviewing it. Roach is bowling from wide of the crease, but is quite full. The ball beats the inside edge, was hitting the top of the middle stump, but less than half of the ball hit him in front of the stumps

Roach has four. Or has he? Ramdin has claimed this catch, but he is not in control of the further release of the ball. Short of a length, outside off, Misbah follows it, gets an inside edge towards the left of Ramdin who dives to catch it cleanly, but at some point between hitting the ground and getting up, he has lost the ball. Ramdin thinks he has controlled the ball for long enough, but he also needs to have a control over the further release of the ball
short of a length, outside off, left alone
short of a length, outside off, slashes at it, fortune running Pakistan's way in the last five minutes. Misbah is dropped, and Jamshed edges this wide of second slip
short of a length, on off, worked to leg for two
length ball outside off, left alone
short of a length, outside off, left alone
short of a length, just outside off, defended solidly
length ball outside off, left alone
another lbw appeal as this one hits him in front of middle, but Misbah - stuck on the crease - has got an inside edge. Erroneously called a leg-bye
left alone outside off, but this pitched on off and angled away. Quite a close leave
good work from Pollard at point. This is punched square, Pollard is going to his left, but realises late he has moved too far so he sticks the right hand to prevent any runs
driven on the up, nicely timed too, but can't beat cover
short of a length, on off, defended off the back foot
and Misbah is off the mark with the first non-Roach delivery he faces. Bunts a length ball into the leg side
short of a length, angling in from round the stumps, defended back to him
swinging into the pads, Jamshed drives, but misses
length ball, angling into the pads, at gentle pace, and is nicely clipped away past midwicket for four
short of a length, holds its line outside off, left alone
wide length ball, driven on the up, with an open face, gets a single to deep cover
short of a length, outside leg, worked away for an easy single
short of a length again, turning in, cramps him up. Defended
short of a length, 87ks, gradually he is getting faster and faster. Defended back to him
nicely punched away past cover for two
short, wide, cut away to two-thirds deep point for one
short of a length, on the stumps, defended back to him
short leg began to move before Misbah had even played. this is illegal according to the laws. Misbah was playing the paddle, Pollard got to the mis-hit, but couldn't catch it
defended off the front foot
another defensive
short of a lenght, worked into the leg side for one
carrom ball, Misbah seems to have picked it only after pitching. Defended from the crease
short, wide, cut away to deep point for one
length ball outside off, defended to cover
angling in from wide of the crease, gets an inside edge onto the pad. Bravo is the only man appealing
length ball outside off, driven to the left of cover, but can't beat Samuels
into the pads, worked away square on the leg side for a couple
slower ball, Misbah is way early into the drive, gets a thick inside edge, but is safe
on a length, in front of off, defended to cover
short, no turn, punched to long-on
appeal for lbw, but this is pitched outside leg
flighted on off, driven to long-off for one
offbreak, starts outside off, defended off the back foot
quicker, carrom ball, Misbah is squared up in defence
flighted on off, defended to short midwicket
short of a lenght, on off, defended back to him
driven on the up, but straight to mid-off
pushed wide of point for a single
short of a length, outside off, angling in, they drop and run. Pakistan need more of this. That ball had hardly gone anywhere
drives on the up, but can't beat cover
length ball, on off, angling away, hits the outside half of the bat for a single to third man
half-volley just outside off and Jamshed drives this over that short field. Inside-out he goes. First boundary since the 12th over
short offbreak, beats the defensive push
defended off the front foot
left alone as this is pushed outside off
punched away to deep cover
short and wide, cut away in front of square for a couple
length ball, outside off, some seam away, beats the drive
length ball, on the pads, defended to leg
short of a length, on off, pushed back to him
full, on off, driven to sweeper-cover for one
on a length, pushed to the left of mid-on for a quick single

dropped. But Ramdin is not appealing here (sorry, this comment is a bit cruel). Drives at a ball away from the body. It is not a half-volley either. Gets an edge, to the left of Ramdin, who dives, but doesn't even reach it. So it is not even a drop
low full toss, clipped off the toes
length ball, into the pads, nicely deflected away fine of fine leg. Run rate crosses three an over
defended off the front foot this time
moves across to leave this shortish delivery outside off
wide length ball, pushes at it for a single to third man
wide length ball outside off
pushed to deep cover for one
short of a length, middle and leg, pushed to mid-on
on the pads, short of a length, worked away for a single
full, middle and off, clipped off the toes after moving across
defended to cover
driven on the up, nicely so, but can't beat cover
Misbah has moved across and missed the line, but thankfully for him it is headed down leg
wide outside off, left alone
moves across to defend this off the front foot
that would have been a wide had he not cut this to deep point for one. Fifty for the partnership
slower ball, pushed to point. Nasir wants one, but is sent back
short of a length, pitched outside leg, worked to deep midwicket for one
wide of the crease, on the pads, clipped away for one
short of a length, on off, defended off the back foot
short of a length, angling in, defended with an open face
short of a length, outside off, defended to point
short of a length, outside off, left alone
tucked away off the hip for one
wide of the crease, angling in, defended off the front foot
tuk, tuk, tuk, tuk, tuk, bang, tuk, tuk, tuk, tuk. Oh Misbah we love you for that. Out of the blue, he makes up his mind that this length ball has to go. And go it does. Over long-off for a clean six
and back to defending
slower ball, Misbah moves across and gloves this around the corner
tucked away off the hip
defended off the front foot, but wide of cover
short of a length, angling in, tucked away for one
length ball, outside off, pushed back to Roach
short, angling away, Jamshed throws his arms at it, gets a thick edge fine of third man for four
tucked away off the hip again
full and wide, driven to deep cover
short of a length, angling towards the off stump, defended to cover
short of a length, outside off, opens the face on it, gets a single to third man
short of a length, outside off, punched to deep point
driven to deep cover
angling away, driven to sweeper-cover again
short of a length, from really wide of the crease, punched away to deep cover for another single
nicely clipped away, but can't beat short midwicket
short, wide, cut away to deep cover
defended to mid-off
another defensive shot
played around the corner on the leg side
defended wide of cover
short of a length, widish, punched away to deep cover
flighted on off, pushed down the ground for one
flighted offbreak, solidly defended
quicker and flatter, defended to cover
on a length, on off, turning away, pushed to cover
pushed wide of point for one

Misbah is trying the reverse-sweep, and the slip is moving to his right even before he has struck the ball. The fielders needed to be warned for this. Placed wide of the slip at any rate, and he gets four for it
flighted outside off, driven to deep cover
full, on off, worked to leg for one
short of a length, outside off, worked wide of mid-on for another single
worked into the leg side for one
short of a length, outside off, pushed to point
fifty for Jamshed. Important innings. Pakistan have recovered well. Cut away to deep point
fullish, on the pads, defended to leg

Jamshed has thrown it away. This is not what Pakistan do. I think he is trying to drive this inside-out over cover, but he hasn't reached the pitch of the ball and ends up lobbing it to Rampaul at long-off
carrom ball, short of a length, defended back to him
short of a length, outside off, punched away to deep point
soft dismissal. Golden duck. good field placement, though. Hard hands by Malik as the ball dips on him, he fails to keep it down and Bravo takes the catch at short midwicket
quick carrom ball, beats the edge, Ramdin whips the bails off. We go to the third umpire, but Akmal is safe
tries the reverse-paddle, but is beaten and is hit on the body
shortish, flat, defended from the crease
fired into the pads, worked away for a single
tries the orthodox paddle, is beaten, and is hit on the body
defended back to Samuels
short, on off, cut away to deep point
offbreak, short, punched back to him
flighted, full, on off, defended back to him
short, on off, cut away to deep point
flighted outside off, pushed wide of the diving short midwicket for one
carrom ball. Akmal has not picked it, and has edged it. It is short, Akmal thinks he can cut it, but he is playing for the offbreak, and thus ends up edging it off the lower part of the bat
another carrom ball, Wahab hasn't read it, and has nearly edged it
Misbah brings up his fifty with a stylish cut. This is short and wide, but he has to beat third man who is quite square. he does that, and beats the point fielder inside the circle too
short of a length, angling in, hits the inside half of the bat for one
short of a length, angling in towards middle and leg, extra bounce hits the high part of the bat
short of a length, wide outside off, left alone
short of a length outside off, he lets it be again
short of a length, but too straight, and he gets inside its line to tuck it away to fine leg
on a length, on off, defended off the back foot
short of a length, into the pads, worked away for one
full, on off, defended back to the bowler
short of a length, on off, defended back to him
length ball, into the pads, defended back to him
defended to cover
short of a length, just outside off, defended
punched away to the left of deep point for two
short of a length, rising towards the chest, fended away into the leg side for a single
short of a length, into the ribs, fended away, but it bounces short of leg gully
short of a length, on off, pushed to the right of deep cover for two
short of a length, into the pads, a defensive push ends Roach's superb work for the day: 10-4-28-3... should have been four but for Ramdin. And cameras
short of a length, worked into the leg side for one
too straight, worked to deep square leg for one
short of a length, outside off, dabbed away to third man for one
another dab to third man
short of a length, just outside off, defended from the crease
short of a length, just outside off, pushed to deep cover for one

Wahab is run out for backing up too far. Slower ball, on off, driven hard and back down the ground. Bravo stretches out to try to field, and gets a touch on it. The ball hits the stumps at the non-striker's end, and Riaz is well out. Please don't call this unfortunate. If you are backing up, you are open to consequences
leg-side full toss, hit straight to square leg. What a miss
another full toss, inside-edged onto the pads
slower ball, pushed wide of long-on, comes back for a second
full toss, and driven to long-on for just the one
short of a length, angling across him, left alone
short of a length, outside off, pushed wide of cover for a single
Rampaul bowls the expected bouncer, but this is to high and called a wide
length ball, on off, defended wide of cover for one
full, into the pads, the fine leg is up, but Roach there makes a diving save to keep them down to one
short of a length, into the body, worked away for one
Ajmal is run out. heaved away straight to Pollard at midwicket, Ajmal wants one, but Misbah doesn't want it, and Ajmal is caught in the middle of the wicket
good bouncer from Rampaul. Gets towards Misbah's throat, who is late into the pull, but the mis-hit doesn't carry to midwicket
beats him with the carrom ball, but doesn't get the edge
defended off the front foot
tossed up, middle and leg, blocked towards mid-on
another forward-defensive
and he defends off the front foot again
carrom ball, hits the outside half of a defensive bat
Misbah backs away, comes back, Rampaul stays straight, and Misbah defends
backs away far, Rampaul stays short of a length and straight. Misbah is beaten on the cut
short of a length, towards the chest, pulled away, but straight to mid-on
bouncer, beats Misbah's hook, who is backing away to make room
short of a length, rising towards the rib cage, dabbed away towards third man for one
on a length, outside off, pushed with an open face
length ball, heaved towards long-on for one
short of a length, rising towards the chest, Junaid drops his wrists on it

Gayle, you beauty. Slower offcutter, Junaid sees a flighted delivery and can't hold himself back. The edge seems it is flying over slip, but Gayle takes a couple of steps back and takes it overhead and behind his body. Superb catch. As he is falling down, he makes sure he doesn't land on his elbow, which can make the ball pop out
yorker for the man on the ladder. Somehow, Irfan gets his bat down in time
short of a length, outside off, left alone
bouncer, angling away, he sways out of its line
defended back to him
on the pads, deflected to short fine leg
fired into the pads, deflected to short fine again
looks to sweep this, beaten
carrom ball, short of a length, defended off the back foot
flighted on off, keeps the strike with a single into the leg side
slower ball, outside off, drilled to long-on, but Misbah doesn't take the single
full toss on the pads, Misbah moves inside it, and smacks this to fine leg for four
drilled to long-on and another single is turned down
driven to mid-off, and this time they take the single. two balls for Irfan to negotiate
slower ball, Irfan is beaten as he defends outside off
and Irfan survives. Pushed to the left of point, but Misbah doesn't take the single and keeps strike
Misbah makes room and sweeps even though Narine has followed him. He hasn't got all of it, but has beaten deep midwicket to his right
short of a length, defended back to him
backs away, Narine tosses it up, and he ends up defending
short of a length, punched to deep point, and he refuses the single
Irfan is nearly run out. he wants a single but the ball is hit straight to short fine leg. But he makes it back in time
Misbah makes room to try to get a single, but he is cramped for room, and Irfan has to face now
short of a length, on off, dabbed away past that second slip for one
backs away to try to hit it to leg, Rampaul bowls the slower ball, and Misbah changes the shot to place it past cover-point for two
what a shot. Misbah has smoked this. Misbah moves across and sets himself up. Rampaul bowls length on off, and he has drilled it over long-off for a six. Fifteen short of a hundred now
low full toss. Yorker gone wrong. Dug out to leg, thinks he can take two, but when he sees the fielder approaching he turns down the one too
Misbah backs away, Rampaul follows him, Misbah moves back, and gets a wide
full, on the toes, clipped away to deep midwicket for one
short of a length. Dead-batted. A huge cheer goes around at The Oval
short of a length, quick, Misbah stays in the crease and defends
Misbah gets six more. Down the wicket to a flighted delivery and lofts it over long-on. Not the best of the timed shots, but he has done enough to beat the man at long-on
backs away, but ends up defending a flat delivery
angling into the pads, deflected to short fine, but doesn't take one
short, flat, punched away wide of long-on for a two that takes him to his personal best
carrom ball, Misbah picks it late, ends up defending it back to him
slower ball outside off, he pushed it to the left of point to take the single that cheers up the Pakistani contingent in the stands

full toss wasted. It was on the pads, he tried to smack it to leg, got an inside edge, but the fine leg is fine, and keeps them down to one. He just ran with the shot here, and was surprised that fine leg was fine
bouncer, rises only chest high, but he fends at it, and is hit on the glove. No short leg in, though
solid defensive as he pitches this short of a length. Another cheer from the stands
bouncer, does well to get it head high. Irfan is beaten on the fend
slower ball, Irfan defends, is beaten on the outside edge. Misbah gets another shot at the hundred and a fighting total
Misbah backs away, Rampaul follows him, he tucks it to fine leg, but doesn't take the one
gets inside the line to tuck this shortish ball away to leg, but another single has been turned down
makes room, Rampaul stays short of a length, he cuts, but finds Bravo at cover-point
pulled away to the left of fine leg, but they get just the one. Two balls for Irfan to face
bouncer, just outside off, easily sways out of its line

Rampaul, you century-denier, you. The perfect short ball, towards Irfan's chest, he can't get out of its way, and gloves it up in the air. Taken nonchalantly at that short leg. Spare a thought for Misbah. Irfan fought hard to help his captain, and is gutted

inn2.comm: length ball, on the pads, clipped away to fine leg
swipes away at it, but the ball is way too short for him, and hits him in the rib cage
length ball, angling across, beats another swipe
another short ball, just outside off, he drops his gloves under it
short again, and he leaves it alone outside off. No point going after his extra bounce
short of a length, outside off, punched wide of mid-off for one
short of a length, middle and off, hits the inside half of the bat
on a length, on off, defended off the front foot
hint of swing after the ball pitches outside leg, beats the inside edge
he has swiped at this one and hoped for the best. Somehow it lobs over the bowler's head for four
short of a length, just outside off, runs off the outside half for one
length ball outside off, he gets under it and drives it inside-out over cover for four
short of a length, outside off, left alone
short of a length, middle and leg, turned to leg
Charles plays at this without looking at this. This is a bouncer, headed towards his helmet, Charles is looking towards mid-on when he hooks it. Taken at fine leg
short of a length, into the ribs, nearly carries to that deepish short leg
again rising towards the ribs, Bravo is on his toes to defend
full, angling in towards off, defended from the crease
swings and misses. Extra bounce, and also came back in. Short of a length, just outside off, seams back in, and Gayle is caught neither forward nor back. Beaten
this one swings away at 142ks, left alone outside off
short of a length, on off, defended to mid-off

huge appeal after a huge inside edge. It's a good delivery, though, seaming in after the awayswinger, but he has got a thick inside edge. Junaid, though, is a serial appealer, and is not likely to die wondering
dug in short, only hip high, and Gayle smashes this with the front leg in the air. It races away for four through square leg
pitched up outside off, gets some swing away. Bravo leaves it alone

Irfan you tall beauty. This is good short-pitched bowling. We might still have a cracker tonight. That is hardly short of a length, but has risen towards the chest, and Bravo tries to drop his bottom hand while fending, but ends up edging it behind
Irfan bowls the change-up full ball. Samuels is caught back, but defends well
short now, into the rib, he jabs at him with the bottom hand off, and it flies wide of that deepish short leg
full, widish, swinging away, Gayle is caught back and is beaten by the swing
slightly wayward, and tucked away off the hip for one
driven on the up, to the right of cover, but Shafiq makes a diving save there. Plus four for him
short of a length, into the pads, defended to leg
fuller, into the pads, beats the inside edge, but it is headed down leg
short of a length, angling in towards off, defened back
pitched in short, too straight this time, and has been deflected fine of fine leg. Called leg-byes. He might have missed it, which explains why it went away so slow
punched away down the ground, and Wahab makes a diving save at mid-on to save three runs. Seven runs saved by the fielders in this over
what a beauty from Irfan. On a length, just outside off, but that bounce is what you get from short of a length. It seams away too. Gayle beaten comprehensively
Gayle is unsettled clearly. Short of a length, outside off, but he goes groping. This is at 145ks, seaming away, at extra bounce. Beaten again
this is a little loose. Not the same sting behind this short ball, but Gayle's punch finds Misbah at short cover
this has bounced towards the helmet of Gayle. It takes some doing. Bowled at 137ks. Gayle fends in front of his face, but with soft hands, and keeps it down too

well done Gayle. He has faced some short-pitched bowling, but the moment bowls the odd fuller delivery, he is ready and swings this clean back over his head. Top cricket. Good on Gayle for not being caught on the back foot
That's lucky. Gayle backs away to try to hit this over the leg side, Irfan follows him, hits his pad, but the fine leg is up, and is beaetn
short of a length, outside off, defended to cover
short of a length, pitches leg, defended in front of off
slightly fuller, solidly defended off the back foot
dug in short, but I think everybody - including me - lost the ball as it came out of Junaid's hand. Good job it is outside off, and is left alone
short of a length, middle and leg, defended to leg
what a shot. That's a scorcher. This is short of a length, but a little too wide, and Samuels stands tall to drive this on the top of the bounce. Through extra cover it rockets away

this is exciting. Gayle backs away, Irfan bowls length, you are anticipating something, and Gayle gets enough bat on it to clear mid-off. This is not middled by a long way, but the mis-hit is powerful enough
what a flick-pull. Short of a length, angling into the hip, he has the front leg in the air, and short-arms this in front of square on the leg side
short again, but it has nothing behind it, and has been picked away for a single into the leg side
short of a length, outside off, Samuels plays inside its line
nearly gets him. Short again, rising towards the chest, Samuels gets an edge on the fend, but it avoids the second slip
short, into the body, Gayle gets a top edge on the flick-pull, but it goes into his chest and dies
on a length, on off, defended off the back foot
full, headed towards middle and leg, defended back to him
super drive. Samuels plays beautifully on the up. This is not driving length at all, but he stands tall, and drives it on the top of the bounce, between the stumps and mid-on
short of a length, on off, punched on the up again, but this time straight to mid-off
wide down the leg side. Bouncer gone wrong
angling in from short of a length, and nearly chops it on the cut
short of a length, angling in towards the top of off. Defended off the back foot
short of a length, flat, worked away for an easy single
offbreak, slightly flat, defended off the back foot
flighted this time, dipping a little, defended off the front foot
slightly shorter, defended off the back foot
flighted outside off, Samuels presses well forward to defend
slower through the air, flighted on off, driven back to Ajmal
short of a length, outside off, punched to deep cover
dug in short, rising towards the chest, Samuels defends with soft hands
short of a length, on off, defended off the back foot
short of a length, outside off, punched away to deep cover for one
good bouncer, at 141ks, gets it shoulder high. Gayle is looking to pull but he has to withdraw because it is too high to control
short of a length, on off, pushed to mid-off and pinches a single
quick ball, no turn, hits the inside edge of the bat. Nearly gets the lbw, but it has run away off the inside half of the bat
shimmies down the wicket to defend this quick ball
short of a length, he goes back to punch this to cover
down the wicket to drive this to long-on for one
short of a length, into the pads, punched down the ground for one
down the wicket to reach the pitch of the ball, and gets a single to long-on
short of a length, on off, defended with an open face
pushed nicely to the right of mid-off for a single
good bouncer, but he has overstepped. At 147ks, it goes head high for Gayle, who sways out of its line just in time
the free hit is full and wide, and is beaten on the big drive
full, into the pads, clipped away to long leg
short of a length, rising towards the chest, punched wide of deep cover for two
short of a length, middle and leg, defended back to him
flighted on off, defended back to him
flatter, into the pads, deflected to short fine leg
slower through the air, on a length, in front of off, defended back to him
even slower, and higher, defended off the front foot
swept away, but finds short fine leg
driven to long-off for one
length ball, middle and leg, pushed wide of mid-on for one
short, outside off, extra bouncer, but he has cut this well over point for four
full outside off, driven to cover
short of a length, outside off, hits the inside half of the bat, but they take a single
slower ball, misses the inside edge, but it is headed down leg
short of a length, into the pads, helped away for one
makes him play back at a ball that is not short enough, but Gayle gets a healthy enough edge to send it past slip
sweeps at this, and just about gets a bottom edge to short fine leg
down the wicket to defend this to shirt midwicket
down the wicket, beaten in the flight, but offers it the pad
Samuels looks to push forward, but the ball is flat. Bunted off the back foot for a single to short leg, which has been facilitated by Riaz's throw to short fine leg
the doosra. Gayle has not picked it. On a length, outside off, Gayle wants to go back over the bowler's head, but the ball turns in to beat the inside edge by a mile and hits the middle stump
short of a length, pushed wide of mid-on for one
short of a length, rising into the ribs, drops it around the corner for one
short of a length, outside off, defended back to Wahab
bouncer this time, on off, head high, beats him on the pull
short-arms this shortish delivery to deep midwicket

terrific delivery. Dug in short, but not too short, gets it to rise higher than the chest. Sarwan is fending uncomfortably, and edges it through to the keeper. Never in control of the bounce. What a match this is turning out to be
nice dip on this, Samuels presses forward to pad this away. Beaten in the flight
shimmies down the track to defend this flat delivery
full, flat, pushed to short midwicket
down the wicket, beaten in the flight by the dip, but defends well
short of a length, turning in, defended to leg
the maiden ends with a forward-defensive after a slight tootsy down the track
bouncer first up, followed by a stare, and a huge cheer from the crowd. Akmal has had to jump this full length to collect this after Pollard sways out of its way
full outside off, left alone
length ball, on off, holds its line, defended back to him
dug in short, outside off, left alone
sucker ball, Pollard is nearly sucked into it. After bowling short, he pushes one full wide outside off. Pollard follows it limply, and is beaten on the push
short of a length, on off, seams away to beat the edge, at 146ks. Last four overs: nine runs and two wickets
down the wicket to drive this wide of mid-off for one
offbreak, full, outside off, defended off the front foot
doosra, doesn't pick it. Short of a length, outside off, holds its line, takes the edge, falls just short of slip
flighted, dipping on him, defended in front of his body
and he doesn't read the doosra again, but it doesn't carry to slip
wide down the leg side. Just fired in
quick offbreak, at 93ks, defended from the crease
sort of a length, hits the bat as opposed to the bat hitting it. Goes to third man for one
short of a length, outside off, angling away. Left alone
short of a length, into the body, defended to midwicket
slower ball gone wrong. A full wide down the leg side. At 101ks
back to quick shortish bowling. Defended back to him off the back foot
slightly shorter, slightly higher, much wider. Left alone
bouncer, on the stumps, Pollard ducks under it. Still 0. Off 16 balls
down the wicket to push this to long-on for one
sharp offbreak after dipping on him. Defended back to him
what a mix-up. Pollard is off the mark. First he doesn't pick the doosra, then ambles across for an easy single wide of point. Samuels, though, hasn't. But despite a late start, Samuels makes it
short, wide, looks to cut, but this one is a doosra too, and he hasn't picked it. Beaten
defended off the front foot
short of a length, turning in, punched away to deep midwicket
down the wicket to push this towards long-on for one
defended off the back foot
another defensive off the back foot
full, flat, pushed to mid-on
short of a length, flat, defended off the back foot
topspinner, on off, kept out by him
short, turning in, helped away around the corner for one
Pollard breaks free. Just a flick. Too full from Ajmal, on the pads, and he has flicked this back over the bowler's head. Nonchalant
slower through the air, dipping on hi, then turns in sharply from outside off, hits him on the pad, but outside the line of off
slightly quicker, doesn't turn in either, hits the outside half of the bat
short of a length, outside off, defended to cover
tossed up on off, defended to cover

Hafeez has got the huge wicket. Samuels has run past one. Quick ball, outside off, on a length, drifts away from Samuels to leave his stranded. Superb bowling. No turn, just the drift away, and the quick pace
full, and stylishly flicked away to short midwicket
flighted outside off, defended away from the body, with an open face
non-turner, Bravo has had to make a late adjustment to defend this in front of off
flighted outside off, driven to short cover for one
short of a length, punched down to long-on for one
short, but down the leg side. Concedes a wide
short of a length, pitched outside leg, defended in front of off
fuller, but not full enough. Left alone outside off
short of a length, on off, angling away, defended to cover
tennis-ball bounce outside off, he goes for the cut, and is beaten by the extra bounce
Pollard dances down the wicket and hopes for the best. He gets a thick edge but it doesn't carry to third man
moves inside the line to bunt this length ball into the leg side for one
length ball, on off, pushed to deep midwicket to bring up the 100
quick, into the pads, helped away for a single around the corner
flighted outside off, defended back to him
offbreak, outside off, blocked off the front foot
swept away from leg to fine leg for one
topspinner, short of a length, punched down the ground, not wide enough of Hafeez
short of a length, just outside off, left alone to angle away
dug in short, rising towards the chest, defended off the back foot
short of a length, outside off, pushed wide of cover for one
length ball outside off, defended from the crease
angling in, tucked off the hip for one
that's nasty. Rises towards the chest from just short of a length, hits the shoulder of the bat, but there is no gully to take this
doosra. Doesn't pick it, but gets a single off the outside half of the bat
flighted outside off, defended back to him
short of a length, dabbed away to backward point where they pick on Irfan
quick and flat, holds its line in front of middle and leg. Watchfully defended back
Pollard smacks this flat over long-off. This is full, and he has drilled it neat. He is picking the hitting balls well
dropped. Pollard doesn't read the doosra, edges it through, but Akmal grasses it. I am sorry, you can;t blame Akmal for that. That was a huge deflection. Shouldn't call this a drop
yorker, outside off, squeezes under Bravo's bat
full, outside off, driven powerfully, but straight to mid-off
short of a length, chest high, outside off, Bravo manages to keep it down
short of a length, angling away outside off, worked to leg with both feet in the air. Gets a single
bouncer, on the stumps, he ducks under it pretty early
short again, just outside off, Pollard sways out of its line
bouncer, but down the leg side. Called wide
short of a length, pitches in front of off, defended just outside off
slashes away at a wide shortish ball. Nowhere near the ball
short of a length, on off, bunted into the leg side for a single
short of a length again, just outside off, defended to mid-off
edged past slip. This one seems to have seamed back in from a short of a length and outside off. It cramps him up, but the edge beats Hafeez. They steal the second to rub it in further
driven powerfully on the up, substitute Abdur Rehman does well to mid-off to dive and get a hand to this. Two runs saved
starts with a length ball, middle and off, angling away, defended just outside off
short of a length, just outside off, pushed off the back foot
short of a length, outside off, covers the line to open the face late, and send it past point for a couple
short of a length, on off, pushed into the leg side for one
bouncer, on off, Pollard does well to sway out of its line
short of a length, holds its line in front of off, hits the inside half of the bat
punched away to deep cover for one
short of a length, on middle and leg, the extra bounce hits him on the thigh pad
no direct hit. They take a quick single to cover, Misbah lets the throw go at Bravo's end, but he is in comfortably
full this time, Bravo covers the line and closes the face to place it for a couple into the leg side
short of a length, outside off, angling away, defended back to him
length ball, outside off, driven on the up to deep cover for one
appeal for lbw, but it is one of those optimistic Junaid ones. This has hit him high on the thigh. Bravo is limping
short of a length, outside off, pushed into the leg side for one
dug in short, Pollard drops his wrists and stays inside the line. Collected chest-high by Akmal
dug in short again. Lets out a huge grunt as he puts in the effort. Left alone well outside off again
gloved over the keeper's head. This bouncer was at his body, Pollard tried to pull, was late into it, but is lucky enough to avoid the keeper
short of a length, pitched outside leg, pushed wide of mid-on for one
Poallrd backs away and charges at him, and drives it solidly past cover for a four. This is a scintillating shot
short of a length, outside off, left alone

Riaz strikes. This game is alive still. Extra bounce for Riaz. He has bowled his heart out today. Short of a length, steep bounce, on off, rises towards the chest again, and takes the edge through. Shoulder of the bat. A good restrained hand from Pollard
length ball, outside off, left alone
another leave outside off. Ramdin is cautious here
fuller still, on off, defended back to him. Riaz threatens to throw it back at him. Good aggression. This match is on
offbreak, worked past short leg for a single
edged wide of slip. Ramdin has no clue about this doosra. It starts middle and leg, takes the leading edge, and beats slip. What's more? Ramdin goes off the strike with this three
doosra again. Bravo reads it off the pitch, and defends it outside off
flatter, but not short enough to play the flashy punch that Bravo has played. And he has played it well, wide of point

brain fade for Bravo. He has batted so well for so long, so calmly, but sees this flighted delivery and throws the works at it. This is cleverly bowled. Slow through the air, flighted, dipping, turning in from outside off. Beats the huge sweep, hits him in front of off. This is plumb. Bravo reviews it because he is the last recognised batsman, but this is plumb. Game on
and he smacks the first ball he faces for four through cover. It's short, flat, outside off, and has been dismissed from his presence
length ball outside off, mis-hits the drive, gets a single
dug in short, outside off, Narine stays inside the line
short again, into the body, Narine fends, in the air, but straight of short leg
Narine is playing a blinder. He makes room and hits this leg-stump full toss between point and cover. Seems the yorker has gone wrong, and he has hit this hard into the ground
dug in shirt, fended away through where gully would have been. Takes the single
driven powerfully on the up, gets a single to deep point
full, into the pad, turning down, goes for two leg-byes

Ramdin loves to cut. And he has done it again. This is not too short, and is turning in sharply, but he manages to cut it between the legs of gully. I won't call it a drop because it has gone fast, but he should have stopped it at least
doosra, starts outside leg, hits the pad, and goes for two
flighted on off, driven back at him, hits the stumps at the non-striker's end, but Ajmal hasn't got a hand to it
flat, outside off, defended solidly back to him
another sharp offbreak not short enough to cut. Ramdin tries it, and is beaten this time
short, into the body, Narine flicks this over midwicket for two. He is playing a lovely cameo here

bouncer, just outside off, left alone. Will you believe this? Pakistan have only seven to defend, but they don't have enough fielders inside the circle. Called a no-ball. Well done Nigel Llong. Alert. No free hit, though

Pakistan stay alive. This game stays alive. Long live ODI. Narine backs away to drive, the ball is not short enough, the extra bounce gets the edge. Akmal hasn't dropped anything today, he is not about to now
a nervous nervous push outside off. Full, sucker ball. Roach is nearly sucked into it, but doesn't edge it
what a beauty. A 140k yorker from that height. On off. Well done, Roach too for keeping it out
short of a length, outside off, angles away, Roach plays inside the line of it
it is a dot. Short of a length, middle and leg, defended off the back foot. Well done, Roach
short of a length, cut away to third man for one
Malik adds a lazy attempt at point to his golden duck. The misfield not only gives them one, but it takes Roach off strike too
short of a length, middle and leg, drops it to leg and takes a single
how fitting that Roach has finished it all. Length ball outside off, Roach square-drives it over point for the winning runs. That to go with his 10-4-28-3
